# Caddy reverse proxy — TLS termination for the Portainer deployment
# --------------------------------------------------------------------
# Why this exists:
#   The app container serves plain HTTP. Modern browsers (Chrome HTTPS-First)
#   aggressively upgrade http:// → https:// for any hostname, which breaks the
#   Google OAuth callback (browser hits https on an http-only server →
#   ERR_EMPTY_RESPONSE). Render works because Render terminates TLS for us.
#   Caddy does the same here: it terminates HTTPS and proxies to the app.
#
#   `tls internal` issues a self-signed cert from Caddy's local CA. The browser
#   shows a one-time "not private" warning — click Advanced → Proceed once and
#   the cert is trusted for the session. For a warning-free cert, install
#   Caddy's root CA (in the caddy_data volume) on client machines.
#
# If the host/port ever changes, edit the site address below.

{
	auto_https disable_redirects
}

192.168.21.220.nip.io:3001 {
	tls internal
	reverse_proxy app:3000
}
